# Design Philosophy

**Before any UI, interaction, visual, or UX decision, read [`docs/design-philosophy.md`](../../docs/design-philosophy.md).**

## Principles

Users are not filling out forms. They are creating ideas.

- Reduce friction in every interaction; never add it.
- Let the interface disappear into the background.
- Content is always the hero.
- Feel like a modern AI creative studio — not an enterprise management system.
- Think **creation**, not **configuration**.
- Every pixel should help users think, not remind them they are using software.

## When this applies

- New or changed screens, components, layouts, copy, or flows
- Styling, spacing, typography, color, and motion
- Form vs. creative-workflow tradeoffs
- Any design review or UX critique
